      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 337: 🟡 Suggestion: `addConversationRequest` is documented as requiring `conversationsRequestsMtx_` to be locked, but it now calls `isRemovedGroupConversation` which independently locks `convInfosMtx_`. While the lock ordering appears safe (requests → conversations → convInfos), this implicit cross-mutex dependency introduced inside a method documented for single-mutex use should be noted in the comment to prevent future deadlocks.\n```suggestion\n        // conversationsRequestsMtx_ MUST BE LOCKED\n        // Note: isRemovedGroupConversation internally locks convInfosMtx_\n        if (isConversation(id) \u0026\u0026 !isRemovedGroupConversation(id))\n```",
