      "message": "Line 2008: 🟡 Suggestion: `rmConversationRequest` is called unconditionally, but if `isConversation(convId)` returned true, the conversation was already accepted previously and there is likely no pending request to remove. This call will needlessly invoke `saveMetadata()` and `saveConvRequests()` (disk I/O) even when there is nothing to erase. Consider guarding it:\n```suggestion\n        if (pimpl_-\u003egetRequest(convId) !\u003d std::nullopt)\n            pimpl_-\u003ermConversationRequest(convId);\n```\nAlternatively, make `rmConversationRequest` itself no-op when the key is absent (skip the saves).",
